WEBVTT

00:09.931 --> 00:13.172
- The name of the game
is "Mafia."

00:13.241 --> 00:15.275
♪ ♪

00:17.827 --> 00:19.275
Was there a syllabus
I was supposed to read?

00:20.931 --> 00:22.517
- He just needs you
to explain the rules.

00:22.586 --> 00:24.034
- Don Ridley,
you have been going

00:24.103 --> 00:25.758
to Tina Brown's
game night for years.

00:25.827 --> 00:27.379
Are you telling me
you never played Mafia?

00:27.448 --> 00:28.655
Do you still work
for "Vanity Fair"?

00:28.724 --> 00:31.068
- Uh, sometimes "VF,"
sometimes "GQ."

00:31.137 --> 00:33.310
- Oh, everyone wants
a piece of Don Ridley.

00:33.379 --> 00:35.758
Okay, quick rules refresher.

00:35.827 --> 00:38.137
You have all chosen either "T"
for "townsperson,"

00:38.206 --> 00:39.793
or "M" for "murderer."

00:39.862 --> 00:42.000
Each round, the murderer
will kill someone,

00:42.068 --> 00:45.448
and the townspeople must root
out who he or she is.

00:45.517 --> 00:47.379
Now, heads down.
Eyes closed.

00:49.310 --> 00:53.137
Murderer awaken.
Choose your prey.

00:53.206 --> 00:57.862
♪ ♪

00:57.931 --> 00:59.241
Thank you, murderer,
head down.

00:59.310 --> 01:00.931
Townspeople,
you may wake up.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.827
While you were sleeping,
Zane was brutally murdered.

01:03.896 --> 01:06.827
- Oh.

01:09.206 --> 01:12.551
- Now figure out who did it.

01:12.620 --> 01:15.344
- I think that it was Liza.
- I think Kelsey's drunk.

01:15.413 --> 01:17.655
- Yeah, how do we know
it wasn't you, Peters?

01:17.724 --> 01:19.241
- Can you please go get me
another glass of wine?

01:19.310 --> 01:21.655
Okay, Liza already killed you.
- I didn't.

01:21.724 --> 01:23.103
And no one's seconded.

01:23.172 --> 01:25.103
- Liza's lying.

01:25.172 --> 01:26.689
I can tell.

01:28.655 --> 01:32.241
Well, it is a game.
Isn't it?

01:32.310 --> 01:36.068
I mean, it could be anybody.
It could be you.

01:36.137 --> 01:38.724
- Oh, so I accuse you,
then you accuse me.

01:38.793 --> 01:41.379
That is textbook
guilty behavior.

01:41.448 --> 01:43.827
- Kelsey accused me first.
And I did not accuse her.

01:45.206 --> 01:47.206
- The killer would
stay off the radar.

01:47.275 --> 01:50.344
Let someone else accuse,
and then pounce.

01:50.413 --> 01:51.379
Like you did.

01:51.448 --> 01:53.586
- You sound paranoid.

01:53.655 --> 01:56.344
And guilty.

01:56.413 --> 01:57.689
- Other townspeople
can weigh in.

01:57.758 --> 01:58.896
- But let's assume
you're right.

01:58.965 --> 02:00.689
If Kelsey is the killer,

02:00.758 --> 02:02.206
wouldn't she have
thought of that?

02:02.275 --> 02:06.896
- No, she's right.
I'm...kind of drunk.

02:06.965 --> 02:08.965
- Uh, plus, we all heard your
cufflink clink your glass

02:09.034 --> 02:10.310
when you pointed at Zane.

02:10.379 --> 02:12.620
I heard it.

02:12.689 --> 02:16.241
Uh, is anyone else
even wearing cufflinks?

02:16.310 --> 02:18.172
- There was no sound.

02:18.241 --> 02:21.103
This is--
- Ah, he's turning red.

02:21.172 --> 02:22.586
Seconded.

02:22.655 --> 02:25.275
He's so guilty.

02:25.344 --> 02:26.724
Sorry, Charles.
- Okay, all right.

02:26.793 --> 02:28.517
Enough debate.
We have two nominees.

02:28.586 --> 02:30.620
Now, just remember that
whoever you vote to accuse...

02:30.689 --> 02:32.034
...dies.

02:32.103 --> 02:34.379
So, who thinks it was Charles?

02:34.448 --> 02:35.551
- Ooh.

02:35.620 --> 02:39.931
- Oh, wow.
And who votes Liza?

02:40.000 --> 02:43.103
Charles, you are dead.
Oh, okay.

02:43.172 --> 02:46.586
So were you a townsperson
or a murderer?

02:47.965 --> 02:49.827
- Townsperson.

02:49.896 --> 02:51.758
The murderer
is still at large.

02:51.827 --> 02:54.206
- Okay, heads down.
Eyes closed.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.931
If you have been killed,
you can keep your eyes open.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.931
Murderer awaken,
choose your victim.

03:03.068 --> 03:09.620
♪ ♪

03:09.689 --> 03:12.379
- So no sex for 90 days,
like, at all?

03:12.448 --> 03:14.517
- I don't know, I just feel
like I have to do a full reset.

03:14.586 --> 03:18.000
No sex, no alcohol,
maybe no gluten.

03:18.068 --> 03:19.586
- I-I don't know, I just feel
like there's steps

03:19.655 --> 03:22.586
that you skipped over that
are less Amish than this.

03:22.655 --> 03:24.379
- Amish.

03:24.448 --> 03:25.931
- Hey, I'm gonna tie up my dog
here while I use the head.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.344
Is that okay?

03:27.413 --> 03:29.931
Come here, good boy.
Come here.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.448
Come here.
What's your name?

03:31.517 --> 03:33.172
Oh, hi, Hawkeye.

03:33.241 --> 03:35.034
- Soak it up.
Those are the last face licks

03:35.103 --> 03:37.103
you're getting this year.
- Shut up.

03:37.172 --> 03:39.068
Hi, where's your dad going,
huh?

03:42.689 --> 03:44.000
- Ew.
Water?

03:44.068 --> 03:45.689
Yeah.

03:45.758 --> 03:47.586
- When you left, you were
going to get me wine.

03:47.655 --> 03:49.344
- When I left,
you were upright.

03:49.413 --> 03:51.034
- Well...

03:51.103 --> 03:52.655
I'd rather take a nap here
than on the train.

03:52.724 --> 03:54.137
- You can crash at mine

03:54.206 --> 03:56.379
if you don't wanna
go back to Brooklyn.

03:56.448 --> 03:58.172
What?
What?

03:59.689 --> 04:01.241
- Nothing.

04:01.310 --> 04:03.586
It's just we haven't
really spoken since D.C.

04:03.655 --> 04:06.517
I said "crash," not "smash."

04:06.586 --> 04:10.586
- They're synonymous.
- That is presumptuous.

04:10.655 --> 04:11.827
- I'll think about it.

04:11.896 --> 04:14.000
- Well, don't think too long.

04:14.068 --> 04:16.379
- I'll think about it
for five minutes.

04:16.448 --> 04:18.551
And then I'll meet you there.

04:18.620 --> 04:22.413
Go, go, go,
before I change my mind.

04:27.413 --> 04:29.000
- Solid Mafia skills.

04:31.379 --> 04:33.206
I need a date for
Tina Brown's next week.

04:33.275 --> 04:36.034
Just don't write down anyone's
name who's actually there.

04:36.103 --> 04:38.586
Tobey Maguire ruined that
for everybody.

04:38.655 --> 04:40.896
Um, never played.

04:40.965 --> 04:42.379
But, you should ask Diana.

04:42.448 --> 04:44.793
She's, uh--
she's great at Celebrity.

04:44.862 --> 04:48.206
- Looks like her
dance card is full.

04:48.275 --> 04:50.310
So, is it a date?

04:50.379 --> 04:53.068
- Uh, I'm not really
dating right now.

04:53.137 --> 04:54.413
Long story.

04:54.482 --> 04:57.068
- Mm, yep.

04:58.379 --> 04:59.896
Last shot.

04:59.965 --> 05:01.827
The "People" Ones to Watch
party is tomorrow.

05:01.896 --> 05:03.413
Don't think of it as dating.

05:03.482 --> 05:05.758
It's...plus-one-ing.

05:05.827 --> 05:08.068
- Liza.

05:08.137 --> 05:10.965
Can I see you in--
in the powder room, please?

05:11.034 --> 05:15.931
- Gotta go.
Nice to meet you...Don.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.482
♪ ♪

05:23.517 --> 05:27.724
♪ ♪

05:31.137 --> 05:35.310
♪ ♪

05:35.379 --> 05:37.586
Oh.

05:37.655 --> 05:39.448
Oh, my God.

05:39.517 --> 05:42.827
Oh, uh, okay.

05:42.896 --> 05:44.965
Okay,
I'll get a plumber in here.

05:45.034 --> 05:47.068
You just--you just get back to
those men you were talking to.

05:47.137 --> 05:48.793
- Carder and Aaron left.
Together.

05:48.862 --> 05:51.103
This party, like my marriage,
is too gay for its own good.

05:51.172 --> 05:53.689
I am officially euthanizing it.
- No. No, no, no. You can't.

05:53.758 --> 05:55.310
It's still early.

05:55.379 --> 05:57.172
- You will realize this once
you're old enough

05:57.241 --> 05:59.517
to rent a car, but one day, men
won't just fall into your lap.

05:59.586 --> 06:01.586
You have to put in an effort.
And it is exhausting.

06:01.655 --> 06:03.551
- No, sorry,
you are not giving up

06:03.620 --> 06:06.655
when there is a room full
of eligible straight men.

06:06.724 --> 06:08.965
Now, go.
It's just a clogged toilet.

06:09.034 --> 06:11.206
It happens all the time.

06:12.965 --> 06:15.620
- I checked the kitchen,

06:15.689 --> 06:17.586
the dumpsters, the bathroom.

06:17.655 --> 06:19.655
I didn't see that Murray Hill
douchebag anywhere.

06:19.724 --> 06:21.241
And they literally
locked the door behind me.

06:21.310 --> 06:22.862
- Well, we can't
just leave him here.

06:22.931 --> 06:25.137
Hey, you wanna come bunk
with me or what?

06:25.206 --> 06:26.724
- I just wanna remind you,
the last time you picked up

06:26.793 --> 06:28.482
a stray, you married her.

06:28.551 --> 06:30.034
Thank you for reminding me.

06:30.103 --> 06:31.551
I really appreciate that.

06:31.620 --> 06:32.896
God.
- He's cute.

06:32.965 --> 06:34.103
Guys, come on,
come on, come on.

06:34.172 --> 06:35.862
- Hey, come on.
- Come on.

06:40.379 --> 06:42.310
It's about time.

06:42.379 --> 06:44.000
I've been waiting
forever for...

06:45.275 --> 06:47.758
Enzo.
Hello, uh--

06:47.827 --> 06:50.172
- Hey.

06:50.241 --> 06:52.413
Bathroom still
in the same place?

06:52.482 --> 06:55.241
Yeh...yeah.

06:59.758 --> 07:06.862
♪ ♪

07:14.137 --> 07:16.586
- It's an easy fix.
15, 20 minutes tops.

07:16.655 --> 07:18.413
- Yeah, well, no rush.

07:18.482 --> 07:21.206
Can I get you a drink?
I just had a party.

07:21.275 --> 07:24.379
- Yeah, your, uh,
toilet told me.

07:24.448 --> 07:25.620
I'm good.

07:28.482 --> 07:32.034
- So, how--um--how--
how've you been?

07:32.103 --> 07:34.241
You don't have to do that.

07:34.310 --> 07:36.413
You disappeared
over a year ago.

07:36.482 --> 07:39.103
I got the hint.
- I didn't, I--okay.

07:39.172 --> 07:41.620
I did. I'm sorry.
Um...

07:41.689 --> 07:43.310
...sorry.

07:43.379 --> 07:45.586
I assumed you had plenty of...

07:48.241 --> 07:49.620
I don't usually--

07:49.689 --> 07:51.413
- Oh, I know, we both said
that many times,

07:51.482 --> 07:52.965
very convincingly.

07:53.034 --> 07:55.310
- I meant it.

07:55.379 --> 07:57.862
You know, I was gonna ask you
out, but you stopped answering,

07:57.931 --> 07:59.379
so...

07:59.448 --> 08:02.000
- Well, I was seeing someone.

08:02.068 --> 08:03.655
- Ah.

08:03.724 --> 08:06.965
- But now I'm not, so...

08:07.034 --> 08:08.482
- I guess
you're out of excuses.

08:10.413 --> 08:12.000
- I guess I am.

08:17.689 --> 08:20.172
- Okay.

08:20.241 --> 08:22.344
- I'll pick you up.

08:22.413 --> 08:25.034
♪ ♪

08:25.103 --> 08:29.827
- ♪ Yeah, aye ♪

08:29.896 --> 08:31.172
- ♪ Shoot ♪
- ♪ Yeah, aye ♪

08:31.241 --> 08:33.310
- Okay, you have a budget
meeting at 2:00,

08:33.379 --> 08:36.034
followed by the YA presentation
with publicity at 3:30.

08:36.103 --> 08:37.586
And then that call with
the Whitney board right after.

08:37.655 --> 08:39.000
You got all that?
- Not a word.

08:39.068 --> 08:41.103
That's why I have you.
And who is this for?

08:41.172 --> 08:42.758
- Liza Miller.

08:42.827 --> 08:45.827
- Gotta be kidding me.

08:45.896 --> 08:48.310
Don Ridley?

08:48.379 --> 08:50.344
I throw a party to meet men,
and you get a date out of it.

08:53.103 --> 08:55.172
- Oh, a man just
fell into Liza's lap.

08:55.241 --> 08:57.310
She's going to the "People"
Ones to Watch party.

08:57.379 --> 08:59.172
Typical.

08:59.241 --> 09:00.827
- It is typical
that men in their forties

09:00.896 --> 09:03.827
just want women
in their twenties, right?

09:03.896 --> 09:05.724
- Diana, I'm not going.

09:05.793 --> 09:07.965
- Do I need to pedal you there
myself in a pedicab?

09:10.413 --> 09:13.896
- You should go.
It's a fun party.

09:13.965 --> 09:16.965
Uh, bring Tupperware.

09:17.034 --> 09:18.517
- Uh, what's that
supposed to mean?

09:18.586 --> 09:20.379
- Oh, at Diana's,

09:20.448 --> 09:22.068
when he thought
that nobody was looking,

09:22.137 --> 09:25.310
I saw Don stuff a pork chop
into his pocket.

09:27.034 --> 09:30.206
- Yeah.
Pork chop.

09:30.275 --> 09:32.517
Pocket.

09:32.586 --> 09:35.379
Have fun.

09:38.448 --> 09:40.931
♪ ♪

09:47.379 --> 09:49.931
♪ ♪

09:50.000 --> 09:51.896
- Okay, uh...
- Oh.

09:51.965 --> 09:53.931
- Since I have interviewed
half of these people here,

09:54.000 --> 09:57.655
you can pick one celeb for me
to introduce you to.

09:57.724 --> 09:58.931
If it's Martha Stewart,
we should do it now

09:59.000 --> 10:00.517
before they bring out
the Jaeger luge.

10:00.586 --> 10:02.689
- Why don't you
introduce me to you?

10:02.758 --> 10:04.137
All I know about you
is your writing.

10:04.206 --> 10:05.862
And that you were
born in Pittsburgh.

10:05.931 --> 10:08.655
- You googled me.
Feels like a date move.

10:08.724 --> 10:10.724
Well, as your plus-one,

10:10.793 --> 10:12.896
I did brush up on your work.

10:12.965 --> 10:15.137
Your piece on Rwanda
in "The Atlantic"

10:15.206 --> 10:17.034
was even better
the second time.

10:17.103 --> 10:20.448
- Wow. Usually my dates
just skim my interview

10:20.517 --> 10:22.586
with Jen Aniston
and pivot to Brangelina

10:22.655 --> 10:24.413
the rest of the night.

10:24.482 --> 10:26.068
- Good thing I'm not
one of your dates.

10:26.137 --> 10:28.758
- Yeah.
Good thing.

10:28.827 --> 10:31.965
Walk this way.

10:34.482 --> 10:37.827
- You really don't like that
train ride to Brooklyn, do you?

10:39.896 --> 10:43.310
- You were wearing
a different shirt earlier.

10:43.379 --> 10:45.965
- I, uh, spilled something.

10:46.034 --> 10:48.137
- You don't spill.

10:48.206 --> 10:49.896
- Yeah.

10:49.965 --> 10:51.344
Do you have a date?

10:51.413 --> 10:54.896
- I have drinks with
a junior editor as Knopf.

10:54.965 --> 10:56.413
- Synonymous.

10:56.482 --> 10:58.482
- Presumptuous.

10:58.551 --> 11:00.413
It's none of my business.

11:00.482 --> 11:02.000
I'm just gonna keep
reading my book.

11:02.068 --> 11:05.379
- Mm, weren't you, uh,
reading the other one?

11:05.448 --> 11:07.655
- I like to read
a few at a time.

11:07.724 --> 11:09.241
I assume that's okay with you?

11:09.310 --> 11:10.551
- Eh.

11:10.620 --> 11:13.103
None of my business.

11:16.034 --> 11:17.862
- It'd be a lot easier
to impress you

11:17.931 --> 11:20.275
with my celebrity friends if
you knew who half of them were.

11:20.344 --> 11:23.655
All right, who's that?

11:23.724 --> 11:26.034
- He's trying to buy
an entire floor of Trump Tower

11:26.103 --> 11:28.965
to house a super PAC to elect
Michelle Obama to Congress.

11:30.241 --> 11:31.655
- It's purely out of spite.

11:31.724 --> 11:33.275
But he's got funding
from Rosie O'Donnell.

11:33.344 --> 11:35.000
- When's this article
coming out?

11:35.068 --> 11:36.586
- Oh, I could write
a thousand pages on that guy.

11:36.655 --> 11:37.827
He's nuts.

11:37.896 --> 11:39.379
- Well,
when you have a book idea,

11:39.448 --> 11:41.344
you know where to bring it.

11:43.758 --> 11:45.413
Seriously.
I'll pitch it tomorrow.

11:45.482 --> 11:48.413
And it's not just about him.
It's all of elite Manhattan.

11:48.482 --> 11:50.310
It's crazier than
you can imagine.

11:50.379 --> 11:52.000
- Okay.

11:52.068 --> 11:54.448
Come pitch it tomorrow.

11:54.517 --> 11:56.137
4:00 okay?

11:56.206 --> 11:57.931
- 4:00 is great.

11:59.896 --> 12:01.724
Ooh, sushi.

12:01.793 --> 12:04.689
Follow me.

12:04.758 --> 12:10.275
♪ ♪

12:10.344 --> 12:13.241
- I just... I can't believe
somebody can be this shitty.

12:13.310 --> 12:14.862
Now, who would do this
to a dog?

12:14.931 --> 12:16.344
Look at him.
- I know, I know.

12:16.413 --> 12:17.862
He is an actual angel, but

12:17.931 --> 12:19.586
you know we can't have pets
in the building.

12:19.655 --> 12:21.689
- Yeah, well, we can't have
three roommates either.

12:21.758 --> 12:23.517
We just won't tell
the landlord now, will we?

12:23.586 --> 12:24.931
- Rude. Okay, but thank you.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.172
- Hawkeye.
Oh, my God.

12:27.241 --> 12:28.689
Where did you find him?

12:28.758 --> 12:30.689
- Uh, some dude just
left him tied up

12:30.758 --> 12:32.034
outside of a restaurant.

12:32.103 --> 12:35.413
- Ugh, my ex.
Such a prick.

12:35.482 --> 12:37.482
- Here.

12:37.551 --> 12:38.862
Hey, bye, little dude.

12:38.931 --> 12:40.241
I'm gonna miss you.

12:40.310 --> 12:43.103
- You love the hot stranger,
don't you?

12:44.862 --> 12:46.586
Don't you?

12:46.655 --> 12:49.068
- I got him some toys too,

12:49.137 --> 12:50.344
if you wanna go grab them.

12:50.413 --> 12:53.206
They're, uh,
back at my apartment.

12:53.275 --> 12:55.103
- It's actually, um--
it's our apartment.

12:55.172 --> 12:57.413
We live there together.
But--ah--okay, no, no.

12:57.482 --> 13:01.482
Sorry--no, never mind.
Yeah.

13:04.551 --> 13:07.448
- ♪ Go ♪

13:12.137 --> 13:14.068
♪ ♪

13:15.275 --> 13:16.689
- Hawkeye.
- Hawkeye, no.

13:16.758 --> 13:19.172
- ♪ Don't go so slow ♪

13:19.241 --> 13:21.620
- Shut up.
You know Pippa Middleton?

13:21.689 --> 13:23.413
- One flight, five hours,

13:23.482 --> 13:25.655
several mini bottles
of tequila.

13:25.724 --> 13:27.482
She told me her sister was
dating somebody famous.

13:27.551 --> 13:29.103
I wrote it down.

13:29.172 --> 13:32.068
- Wait, wait, you broke
the Will and Kate story?

13:32.137 --> 13:34.448
- Don.
Charles Brooks.

13:34.517 --> 13:36.724
- Uh.

13:36.793 --> 13:38.965
Cufflinks.

13:39.034 --> 13:41.862
I heard you have
quite a book idea.

13:41.931 --> 13:43.931
- Ee--
- Please.

13:46.620 --> 13:48.793
- Um, okay, let's dive in.

13:48.862 --> 13:53.655
Um, this book is about
all the dirty, sexy messes

13:53.724 --> 13:55.551
of Manhattan society--

13:55.620 --> 13:58.724
ambassadors, bankers,
not the boring ones.

13:58.793 --> 14:00.310
Disgraced, famous.

14:00.379 --> 14:01.931
Um, Madoffs--

14:02.000 --> 14:05.896
- So is this a novel
or is it nonfiction?

14:05.965 --> 14:08.896
- I was thinking the latter.

14:08.965 --> 14:10.172
- Huh.

14:10.241 --> 14:13.241
Well,
that could be problematic.

14:13.310 --> 14:15.103
- Can we at least
hear the idea?

14:15.172 --> 14:18.896
- Yeah, these are very
litigious, very wealthy people.

14:18.965 --> 14:21.551
But, uh, continue.
Sorry.

14:21.620 --> 14:24.896
- Oh, I was thinking about
framing the story

14:24.965 --> 14:27.620
around drama
at the Trump Tower.

14:27.689 --> 14:29.517
It's a bloodbath,
but also a microcosm

14:29.586 --> 14:31.206
