- He knows.

15:28.310 --> 15:30.896
- About me.

15:30.965 --> 15:32.551
All of it.

15:32.620 --> 15:35.931
God, Liza. How?

15:36.000 --> 15:37.620
- I don't know.

15:39.517 --> 15:42.000
- Not yet.

15:43.931 --> 15:45.827
So, what,
he's just gonna punish you

15:45.896 --> 15:49.931
and just tank every
author you bring in here?

15:50.000 --> 15:52.448
This is such a mess.

15:52.517 --> 15:54.448
How are we supposed
to do our job?

15:57.551 --> 15:59.758
- I'll handle it.

16:02.896 --> 16:07.310
♪ ♪

16:09.137 --> 16:12.379
- Uh, a little busy right now.
- I'll be quick.

16:12.448 --> 16:15.931
I'm resigning.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
- Close the door, please.

16:23.000 --> 16:24.724
What're you doing?

16:24.793 --> 16:26.758
- This isn't going to work.
You're angry with me.

16:26.827 --> 16:28.931
And you're not gonna like any
writer that I bring in here.

16:29.000 --> 16:30.344
That's going to hobble
Millennial

16:30.413 --> 16:32.172
and probably ruin
Kelsey's career too.

16:32.241 --> 16:35.482
And that's not fair to anyone,
so I'm bowing out.

16:36.620 --> 16:39.034
- The only thing
threatening Millennial

16:39.103 --> 16:41.379
is the lie you've been telling
since you got here.

16:41.448 --> 16:44.172
- You can be mad at me.
I deserve that.

16:44.241 --> 16:47.379
But you can't take it out
on a writer I bring in here.

16:47.448 --> 16:49.931
- It's not what I did.

16:50.000 --> 16:54.068
- No, uh,
personal would be asking if--

16:54.137 --> 16:57.275
if Don dropped a trail of
breadcrumbs from his pocket,

16:57.344 --> 16:59.620
in case you got separated
at the "People" party,

16:59.689 --> 17:03.551
but passing on a half-baked,
poorly-conceived book idea

17:03.620 --> 17:07.206
I didn't like, that's--
that's business.

17:07.275 --> 17:10.241
And I trust you can see
the distinction.

17:10.310 --> 17:13.000
- I do.
- Excellent.

17:13.068 --> 17:14.896
Please close the door
on your way out.

17:17.965 --> 17:20.448
♪ ♪

17:28.241 --> 17:30.655
- Hi.

17:30.724 --> 17:32.896
- I gave him back to his owner,

17:32.965 --> 17:34.517
after I slept with her.

17:34.586 --> 17:38.482
- Yes. You broke your fast.
Let me get you a drink.

17:38.551 --> 17:40.344
- Oh, Mags, I--
- No, no, no, no, no, come on.

17:40.413 --> 17:42.655
90 days without booze or sex?

17:42.724 --> 17:45.034
I haven't done that
since grade school.

17:45.103 --> 17:48.000
You don't need
to reset your system.

17:48.068 --> 17:49.965
You just need to have
a good glass of red wine,

17:50.034 --> 17:51.620
and someone to complain
about girls to.

17:51.689 --> 17:53.931
- Fine, but no gluten.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.655
Turns out I really
do have that allergy.

17:55.724 --> 17:57.172
- That is not real.

17:57.241 --> 17:58.965
And I just smoked a big joint

17:59.034 --> 18:00.758
and ate all the bread
in the house, so you're good.

18:02.448 --> 18:05.172
God,
you make everything better.

18:08.241 --> 18:10.551
♪ ♪

18:10.620 --> 18:12.517
- It's 6:00.
I don't see him.

18:12.586 --> 18:14.241
Well, good night.
- Oh, no, no, no.

18:14.310 --> 18:18.034
You are going on this date.
A man fell on your lap.

18:18.103 --> 18:19.724
- Do you always use
people's words against them

18:19.793 --> 18:23.931
like a drunk toddler?

18:24.965 --> 18:26.862
Oh, my God, I'm going
on a date with my plumber.

18:26.931 --> 18:28.896
- Phew.

18:28.965 --> 18:30.586
Sorry for honking.

18:30.655 --> 18:31.965
I'm driving around
for a half hour

18:32.034 --> 18:33.862
and the only spot
I could find is illegal.

18:33.931 --> 18:35.896
- When you said that you
were picking me up,

18:35.965 --> 18:39.517
I--I--I thought you meant
on foot .

18:39.586 --> 18:41.965
- There's no good
Italian food up here.

18:43.448 --> 18:46.034
- In Manhattan.
Come on.

18:49.103 --> 18:55.965
♪ ♪

19:11.448 --> 19:13.103
Anyone else?

19:13.172 --> 19:16.896
- Just Kelsey.
She was upset at first, but...

19:16.965 --> 19:19.310
- So you've both
been lying to me?

19:19.379 --> 19:21.310
- We thought it was best
for the company.

19:21.379 --> 19:22.586
And we didn't want anyone else
at Empirical

19:22.655 --> 19:24.413
to have to lie too.

19:24.482 --> 19:29.241
- Ah, how thoughtful of you
to spare us all that indignity.

19:29.310 --> 19:31.827
- I'm gonna go.

19:31.896 --> 19:33.620
Have a good night.

19:33.689 --> 19:36.379
- Liza, wait.
J--please.

19:36.448 --> 19:40.068
I should apologize
for crashing your meeting.

19:40.137 --> 19:44.275
Uh, I--I am trying to find
my way around all this,

19:44.344 --> 19:47.689
and I, uh--
I took it out on Don.

19:47.758 --> 19:50.172
And that wasn't fair.

19:50.241 --> 19:52.517
You're good at your job.

19:52.586 --> 19:56.827
Millennial needs you
to survive right now.

19:56.896 --> 19:59.379
And I--I don't wanna
jeopardize that.

20:02.448 --> 20:04.034
And that's all
I wanted to say.

20:04.103 --> 20:05.620
Good night.

20:05.689 --> 20:08.620
- Please, just let me explain.

20:08.689 --> 20:10.758
Maybe if you get to know me.

20:10.827 --> 20:12.862
The real me.

20:12.931 --> 20:15.413
- I--I don't think
that's a good idea.

20:15.482 --> 20:18.482
- I'm so sorry
that I lied to you.

20:18.551 --> 20:20.896
I just--I care about you
so much.

20:20.965 --> 20:22.586
I--I need you to know that.

20:22.655 --> 20:26.068
- And I need you
to forget about it.

20:26.137 --> 20:33.137
♪ ♪

20:40.000 --> 20:41.689
♪ ♪

20:41.758 --> 20:44.689
- This restaurant is lovely.

20:44.758 --> 20:46.344
- Try to sound less surprised.

20:46.413 --> 20:49.275
- I'm sorry, it's just--
- Staten Island.

20:49.344 --> 20:53.206
We've got nice places too.
You just never tried 'em.

20:53.275 --> 20:55.482
Amy, we didn't order that.

20:58.000 --> 21:02.344
- Compliments of Mr. De Rosa.

21:02.413 --> 21:06.137
♪ ♪

21:06.206 --> 21:07.724
- No, nothing.

21:07.793 --> 21:10.448
Just, the other night
at my party we played Mafia.

21:10.517 --> 21:12.068
And now...

21:12.137 --> 21:13.482
- Okay, two things.

21:13.551 --> 21:16.482
One, don't say that
out loud again.

21:16.551 --> 21:20.448
And two,
Mr. D is on the City Council.

21:22.448 --> 21:24.724
- But, I mean, you--
you did something for him?

21:24.793 --> 21:27.275
- Yeah, I put new copper pipes
in his summer house.

21:27.344 --> 21:30.103
Turned it around quick so he
could throw a campaign event.

21:30.172 --> 21:32.689
♪ ♪

21:32.758 --> 21:35.275
- Exquisite.
Who sent this over?

21:35.344 --> 21:36.482
- I did.

21:36.551 --> 21:38.103
- I can't let you
buy that for me.

21:38.172 --> 21:40.344
That is a $500 bottle.

21:40.413 --> 21:44.827
- I know.
I'm trying to impress you.

21:44.896 --> 21:46.379
First date.
Don't get used to it.

21:52.103 --> 21:53.448
♪ ♪

21:53.517 --> 21:55.000
