second entrées.

21:55.068 --> 21:56.896
Maxed out the Empirical expense
account.

21:56.965 --> 21:59.103
Those things are relics.

22:01.724 --> 22:04.068
Oh, thank you.
- Didn't go through.

22:04.137 --> 22:06.482
Would you like
to try another card?

22:06.551 --> 22:08.551
- Uh, okay.

22:10.275 --> 22:13.206
Uh...
Just...

22:13.275 --> 22:15.103
- Yeah.

22:15.172 --> 22:17.172
- Thank you.

22:17.241 --> 22:19.034
- Shit.

22:19.103 --> 22:21.620
This is embarrassing.
I guess I'm a relic too.

22:21.689 --> 22:25.068
You write for "Vanity Fair."

22:25.137 --> 22:27.344
And "Vogue."
- Wrote.

22:27.413 --> 22:29.000
Past tense.

22:29.068 --> 22:31.413
Magazines are dying
even faster than books.

22:31.482 --> 22:35.172
This is what I write now.

22:35.241 --> 22:38.172
- "You won't believe which
of these sexy stars is trans."

22:38.241 --> 22:39.896
Is he?
- Nope.

22:39.965 --> 22:41.793
But you have to click through
19 photos and 6 ads

22:41.862 --> 22:43.620
to find that out.

22:43.689 --> 22:46.827
I'm barely pulling in
what I made in my twenties.

22:46.896 --> 22:49.172
- But you're out at A-list
parties every night.

22:49.241 --> 22:51.206
- Free food.
Open bar.

22:51.275 --> 22:53.172
Gift bags.
.

22:53.241 --> 22:55.275
Oh, God.

22:56.965 --> 23:01.034
- Well, look, none of us is
exactly who we say we are.

23:01.103 --> 23:03.034
I've been there.
I'll get dinner.

23:03.103 --> 23:06.000
- No, I can't.
